headline: UnitedHealth Group Turbulent Year Tests Outlook For 2026 Rebound
summary: UnitedHealth Group, NYSE:UNH, is coming off a year of elevated healthcare costs, a major cybersecurity breach, antitrust litigation, and questions over health claims practices. The company has outlined expectations for a rebound in 2026 after this challenging stretch. Separate scrutiny has emerged over former CEO Stephen Hemsley's investment activity through affiliates, which critics say may pose conflicts of interest.
